summary: I'm usually excited for one or two games a year.
body:
I’m usually excited for one or two games a year.

Like, all year. Before, during and after E3 announcements and individual announcements. Only one or two.

This year, I’m excited for Cyberpunk 2077, Sypro Remaster, One’s Justice, FFVII Remake, KH3, Death Stranding, Assassin’s Creed Odyssy, and Athem.

Games announced this year are really amazing. I actually told someone that knows jackshit about video games to keep and eye out for tv commercials ‘cause I don’t watch tv and I really wanna know if more info is out.

Proud of games this year.

summary: not making fun or anything but i just think it’s funny V has a drink vending machine in her apartment as a not-too-subtle...
body:
not making fun or anything but i just think it’s funny

V has a drink vending machine in her apartment as a not-too-subtle environmental storytelling detail that consumerism and invasive corporate control has gone too far, but i see some people like “lol she has a coke machine in her room! that’s dumb/i want one!”

body:
‘V’ Cyberpunk 2077 OC - Character Info

(Faceclaim: Ruby Rose)

First name: Vida

Last name: Cortez

Alias: ‘V’

Date of birth: 10.12.2054

Gender: Female

Prior Convictions:

- 3x Chip Fraud

- 2x Assault

- 2x Vandalism

- 2x Drug Trafficking

- 1x Eddie Laundering

Education:

- Unknown

Details In Brief:

Vida is intelligent and beautiful; a deadly combination in a place like Night City. A woman of the streets, Vida has an intense hatred of the Corps and all that they stand for, and has a prominent track record of swindling those ‘cold-hearted bastards’ of their corporate cash. Though she will never admit to it out-loud, Vida is, at heart, a woman of the people, preferring to fight for and serve those who ended up at the bottom of life’s barrel.

Childhood hero: Johnny Silverhand

Key Life Event: First Big Kill

Why Night City: Unfinished Business
